The paper proposes a novel algorithmic technique for generating deep Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) and demonstrates its effectiveness on complex visual recognition problems such as CIFAR-10 and ImageNet. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
